<h2>How to Run This Application</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Open a Terminal</strong>
        <p>If using VSCode, open a new terminal by navigating to <code>Terminal > New Terminal</code>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Navigate to the Project Directory</strong>
        <p>Ensure the terminal is in the correct project directory (e.g., <code>C:\Users\Moham\OneDrive\Desktop\WD\Demo11ty</code>).</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If not, use the command:
                <pre><code>cd &lt;Your Directory&gt;</code></pre>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Start the Development Server</strong>
        <p>Run the following command in the terminal to start the Eleventy server:</p>
        <pre><code>npx @11ty/eleventy --serve</code></pre>
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Maintaining the Eleventy/Handlebars Project</h2>
<p>To ensure smooth operation, follow these best practices:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Organize Files:</strong> 
        <ul>
            <li>All relevant files are located in the <code>src</code> directory and should not be removed.</li>
            <li>The <code>dist</code> folder is automatically generated with each build and can be safely deleted if needed.</li>
            <li>Edit <code>eleventy.config.js</code> to customize configurations.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Update Dependencies:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Check for outdated packages with:
                <pre><code>npm outdated</code></pre>
            </li>
            <li>Update dependencies using:
                <pre><code>npm update</code></pre>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Run Locally for Development:</strong>
        <p>Use the following command to test changes live:</p>
        <pre><code>npx @11ty/eleventy --serve</code></pre>
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Reflection</h2>
<p>The project structure and workflow with Handlebars are similar to working with Nunjucks (njk). However, Handlebars' syntax presented challenges, particularly with pagination, due to its lack of built-in looping constructs like <code>for</code> or <code>while</code> loops.</p>

